Citation.sAbstract: Bubble temperatures at 95.8 kPa, over the entire composition range are measured for the binary mixtures formed by decane with cyclohexanone, 1,2-dimethoxyethane, tetrahydrofuran and ortho-, meta- and para-xylenes, making use of a Swietoslawski type ebulliometer. liquid phase composition versus temperature measurements is found to be well represented by the Wilson model.
Citation.sTitle: Bubble temperature measurements on the binary mixtures formed by decane with a variety of compounds at 95.8 kPa
